casebody.data:
John DOE and James Doe, Plaintiffs-Appellants,
v.
Sally J. GILL, Defendant-Appellee. No. 18-0504 Court of Appeals of Iowa. Filed February 6, 2019

DECISION WITHOUT PUBLISHED OPINION

See Iowa R. App. P. 6.904

On interlocutory appeal, the plaintiffs appeal the district court's ruling requiring them to amend or restate their petition to bring their lawsuit in their real names. REVERSED AND REMANDED.

REVERSED. REMANDED.
